==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Milkweed
<hw>Milk"weed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any plant of the genera <gen>Asclepias</gen> and
<gen>Acerates</gen>, abounding in a milky juice, and having its seed
attached to a long silky down; silkweed. The name is also applied to
several other plants with a milky juice, as to several kinds of spurge.
Its leaves are a favorite food source for the larvae of the monarch
butterfly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milkwort</ent>⟦br⟧
